Expand and simplify completely: \begin{align*}
x\left(x(1+x)+2x\right)-3(x^2-x+2)
\end{align*}

generations.generations:
First, expand the expression inside the parentheses:
\begin{align*}
x(1+x) + 2x &= x + x^2 + 2x \\
&= x^2 + 3x.
\end{align*}
Next, distribute the 3 through the parentheses:
\begin{align*}
3(x^2 - x + 2) &= 3x^2 - 3x + 6.
\end{align*}
Now, multiply the $x$ by each term inside the parentheses:
\begin{align*}
x(x^2 + 3x) &= x^3 + 3x^2.
\end{align*}
Finally, combine the expanded terms:
\begin{align*}
x^3 + 3x^2 - 3x^2 + 3x - 6 &=
x^3 + (3x^2 - 3x^2) + 3x - 6 \\
&= x^3 + 0 + 3x - 6 \\
&= x^3 + 3x - 6.
\end{align*}
</reasoning>
<answer>
\boxed{x^3 + 3x - 6}<|eot_id|><|endoftext|>

